I was not able to come up with a test case that breaks with PHPUnit 4.8.8 due to a15d638. Do you have one?

The following could be a patch:

```
diff --git a/src/Util/XML.php b/src/Util/XML.php
index 876bb7b..16c4c0e 100644
--- a/src/Util/XML.php
+++ b/src/Util/XML.php
@@ -100,7 +100,8 @@ public static function load($actual, $isHtml = false, $filename = '', $xinclude
             @chdir(dirname($filename));
         }

-        $document  = new DOMDocument;
+        $document = new DOMDocument;
+        $document->preserveWhiteSpace = false;

         $internal  = libxml_use_internal_errors(true);
         $message   = '';
@@ -200,7 +201,13 @@ public static function xmlToVariable(DOMElement $element)
                 $variable = array();

                 foreach ($element->getElementsByTagName('element') as $element) {
-                    $value = self::xmlToVariable($element->childNodes->item(1));
+                    $item = $element->childNodes->item(0);
+
+                    if ($item instanceof DOMText) {
+                        $item = $element->childNodes->item(1);
+                    }
+
+                    $value = self::xmlToVariable($item);

                     if ($element->hasAttribute('key')) {
                         $variable[(string) $element->getAttribute('key')] = $value;
```

thanks for a patch!

here is test case for a bug:

``` php
<?php

class Phpunit488Test extends PHPUnit_Framework_TestCase {

    public function testXmlComparsionBug() {
        // prerequisites
        $this->assertEquals('4.8.8', PHPUnit_Runner_Version::id());

        $xml1 = <<<XML
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<root>
    <node />
</root>
XML;

        $xml2 = <<<XML
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<root>
<node />
</root>
XML;
        // failing one
        $this->assertXmlStringEqualsXmlString($xml1, $xml2);
    }
}
```
